result.execSummary:
All charges against Wesley Emil Alwin in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Wesley Emil Alwin is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant understands charges, penalties and constitutional rights  Defendant pleas guilty to Ct#3-4,12 in 21CF229 and Ct#3 in 21CF259. Counsel stipulates to factual basis for plea. Court finds a factual basis to accept the plea.  Court finds Defendant is freely, voluntarily and knowingly making plea and waiving constitutional rights. Court finds Defendant guilty to Ct#3-4, 12 in 21CF229 and Ct#3 in 21CF259. Court dismisses Ct#1-2,5-11, 13-14 in 21CF229, 21CF237, Ct#1-2, 4-7 in 21CF259 and 21CF260 and 22CF184. Court orders PSI. ADA Walker is not requesting for bond to be revoked. Court will not revoke bond, Def is on GPS. Court sets sentencing and informs the parties there is a possibility there is a jury trial. Court will remove JT set.
